operations.AssociateAwsAccountWithPartnerAccount: Associates a partner account with your AWS account.
operations.AssociateMulticastGroupWithFuotaTask: Associate a multicast group with a FUOTA task.
operations.AssociateWirelessDeviceWithFuotaTask: Associate a wireless device with a FUOTA task.
operations.AssociateWirelessDeviceWithMulticastGrou: Associates a wireless device with a multicast group.
operations.AssociateWirelessDeviceWithThing: Associates a wireless device with a thing.
operations.AssociateWirelessGatewayWithCertificate: Associates a wireless gateway with a certificate.
operations.AssociateWirelessGatewayWithThing: Associates a wireless gateway with a thing.
operations.CreateDestination: Creates a new destination that maps a device message to an AWS IoT rule.
operations.CreateWirelessGatewayTask: Creates a task for a wireless gateway.
operations.DeleteMulticastGroup: Deletes a multicast group if it is not in use by a fuota task.
operations.DeleteWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition: Deletes a wireless gateway task definition. Deleting this task definition does not affect tasks that are currently in progress.
operations.DisassociateAwsAccountFromPartnerAccount: Disassociates your AWS account from a partner account. If PartnerAccountId and PartnerType are null, disassociates your AWS account from all partner accounts.
operations.DisassociateMulticastGroupFromFuotaTask: Disassociates a multicast group from a fuota task.
operations.DisassociateWirelessDeviceFromFuotaTask: Disassociates a wireless device from a FUOTA task.
operations.DisassociateWirelessDeviceFromMulticastG: Disassociates a wireless device from a multicast group.
operations.DisassociateWirelessDeviceFromThing: Disassociates a wireless device from its currently associated thing.
operations.DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromCertifica: Disassociates a wireless gateway from its currently associated certificate.
operations.DisassociateWirelessGatewayFromThing: Disassociates a wireless gateway from its currently associated thing.
operations.GetLogLevelsByResourceTypes: Returns current default log levels or log levels by resource types. Based on resource types, log levels can be for wireless device log options or wireless gateway log options.
operations.GetMulticastGroupSession: Gets information about a multicast group session.
operations.GetPartnerAccount: Gets information about a partner account. If PartnerAccountId and PartnerType are null, returns all partner accounts.
operations.GetResourceEventConfiguration: Get the event configuration for a particular resource identifier.
operations.GetResourceLogLevel: Fetches the log-level override, if any, for a given resource-ID and resource-type. It can be used for a wireless device or a wireless gateway.
operations.GetServiceEndpoint: Gets the account-specific endpoint for Configuration and Update Server (CUPS) protocol or LoRaWAN Network Server (LNS) connections.
operations.GetWirelessDeviceStatistics: Gets operating information about a wireless device.
operations.GetWirelessGatewayCertificate: Gets the ID of the certificate that is currently associated with a wireless gateway.
operations.GetWirelessGatewayFirmwareInformation: Gets the firmware version and other information about a wireless gateway.
operations.GetWirelessGatewayStatistics: Gets operating information about a wireless gateway.
operations.GetWirelessGatewayTask: Gets information about a wireless gateway task.
operations.GetWirelessGatewayTaskDefinition: Gets information about a wireless gateway task definition.
operations.ListDestinations: Lists the destinations registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListDeviceProfiles: Lists the device profiles registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListFuotaTasks: Lists the FUOTA tasks registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListMulticastGroups: Lists the multicast groups registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListMulticastGroupsByFuotaTask: List all multicast groups associated with a fuota task.
operations.ListPartnerAccounts: Lists the partner accounts associated with your AWS account.
operations.ListServiceProfiles: Lists the service profiles registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Lists the tags (metadata) you have assigned to the resource.
operations.ListWirelessDevices: Lists the wireless devices registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListWirelessGatewayTaskDefinitions: List the wireless gateway tasks definitions registered to your AWS account.
operations.ListWirelessGateways: Lists the wireless gateways registered to your AWS account.
operations.PutResourceLogLevel: Sets the log-level override for a resource-ID and resource-type. This option can be specified for a wireless gateway or a wireless device. A limit of 200 log level override can be set per account.
operations.ResetAllResourceLogLevels: Removes the log-level overrides for all resources; both wireless devices and wireless gateways.
operations.ResetResourceLogLevel: Removes the log-level override, if any, for a specific resource-ID and resource-type. It can be used for a wireless device or a wireless gateway.
operations.SendDataToMulticastGroup: Sends the specified data to a multicast group.
operations.SendDataToWirelessDevice: Sends a decrypted application data frame to a device.
operations.StartBulkAssociateWirelessDeviceWithMult: Starts a bulk association of all qualifying wireless devices with a multicast group.
operations.StartBulkDisassociateWirelessDeviceFromM: Starts a bulk disassociatin of all qualifying wireless devices from a multicast group.
operations.TestWirelessDevice: Simulates a provisioned device by sending an uplink data payload of Hello.
operations.UntagResource: Removes one or more tags from a resource.
operations.UpdateLogLevelsByResourceTypes: Set default log level, or log levels by resource types. This can be for wireless device log options or wireless gateways log options and is used to control the log messages that'll be displayed in CloudWatch.
operations.UpdateMulticastGroup: Updates properties of a multicast group session.
operations.UpdateResourceEventConfiguration: Update the event configuration for a particular resource identifier.
